## Why This Is Asked
Tests deep expertise in troubleshooting cross-cluster Consul Connect failures involving TLS, SPIFFE identities, ALPN negotiation, and service discovery coordination. Requires precise, verifiable debugging steps rather than theoretical approaches.

## Key Concepts
- TLS/ALPN troubleshooting in mTLS service meshes
- SPIFFE identity propagation across sidecars and mesh gateways
- DNS resolution and service registration consistency
- Safe CA rotation procedures and policy synchronization
- gRPC streaming requirements for HTTP/2 ALPN support

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example SPIFFE identity validation in Go
class SpiffeValidator {
  validateIdentity(cert *x509.Certificate, expectedSpiffeId string) error {
    uris := cert.URIs
    for _, uri := range uris {
      if uri.String() == expectedSpiffeId {
        return nil
      }
    }
    return errors.New("SPIFFE identity mismatch")
  }
}
```

## Why This Is Asked

Evaluates expertise in diagnosing complex cross-region service mesh issues involving identity management, policy propagation, and gateway TLS configuration under production load conditions.

## Key Concepts

- SPIFFE identity verification across cloud regions
- Mesh gateway TLS termination and SNI-based routing
- Cross-region intention propagation and ACL token management
- Data-plane TLS handshake observability and certificate validation

## Code Example

```javascript
// Certificate validation for SPIFFE ID consistency
function validateSPIFFECertificate(cert) {
  const spiffePattern = /^spiffe:\/\/[^\/]+\/ns\/[^\/]+\/dc\/[^\/]+\/svc\/[^\/]+$/;

  if (!cert.sanURI || !cert.sanURI.match(spiffePattern)) {
    throw new Error('Invalid SPIFFE ID format in certificate');
  }

  return {
    spiffeId: cert.sanURI,
    trustDomain: cert.sanURI.split('/')[2],
    service: cert.sanURI.split('/').pop(),
    namespace: cert.sanURI.split('/')[4]
  };
}
```

## Debugging Commands

```bash
# SPIFFE identity verification
consul tls cert inspect -secret-id $(consul acl token create -service-name data-collector -description "debug-token")

# Cross-region intention validation
consul intention list -token=<replication-token> --filter "Source==data-collector AND Destination==data-service"

# Gateway TLS configuration audit
consul mesh gateway read -name <gateway-name> | jq '.TLS'
```

